    {
      "id": "e25c38b65572e0e530b144d566b0f2425af16c65",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-09 20:54:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nMy question aside, this patch seems clearly correct.  Without it, the client can restart replay in the wrong state.  This isn't usually a problem, but it seems like a state machine violation.\n\nI think it might be nice to have Andriy's explanation of how the bug occurs from the LU in the commit message:\nstep by step explanation:\n1) server goes to recovery stage 2 (lock replay) with at least 2 clients.\n2) client1 and client 2 send lock relay,\n3) client1 sends final ping\n4) server queues final ping from client1 and set exp_lock_replay_needed to 0\n5) client2 still in lock replay stage (waits for lock replies form server)\n6) client1 reconnects\n7) client1 replays locks from the beginning\n8) assertion fails",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "715f81286df4f8d674ac48252b530bba41593bda",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-09 21:04:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review\n\nPer Cray staff at ORNL, Oleg and James worked on troubleshooting what we think was this issue.  They resolved it by removing LU-793 on the servers, but this patch should fix the client issue.\n\nAdded Oleg to review.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
